Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:26.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs100\t(,\fs110)\frz1\fad(3000,500)\fsp0\fscx120\pos(960,800)\b0\shad0\bord0}地          球          脉          动
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.02,0:00:32.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,辽阔的草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Vast open plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.02,0:00:36.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,广袤无垠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Immense spaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.42,0:00:38.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,万籁俱寂\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eerie silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.74,0:00:45.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而 你若以为这里死气沉沉就大错特错了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But any feeling of emptiness is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.90,0:00:54.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草原维系了我们行星最丰富多彩的生命群落\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The plains of our planet support the greatest gatherings of wildlife on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.38,0:01:04.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这一切最终都依赖于一种生命体的存在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the heart of all that happens here is a single living thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.46,0:01:06.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.26,0:01:16.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种神奇的植物覆盖了地球上四分之一的土地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This miraculous plant covers a quarter of all the lands of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.00,0:01:30.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs140\fsp8\fad(1000,1000)\pos(968 ,900)}辽       阔       草       原
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.25,0:01:42.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,980)\bord0\shad3}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.38,0:01:37.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草地无所不在 一点雨水虽然不足以维系一片森林 却可使一片草地存活下来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grasslands exist wherever there is a little rain, but not enough to sustain a forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.26,0:01:39.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些草原非常辽阔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some are huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.46,0:01:42.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仅中亚的疏树大草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Central Asian Steppe alone
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.54,0:01:46.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,便横跨了地球的三分之一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}extends one third of the way around our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.06,0:01:56.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在夏天 雄鹰可以毫不费力的在热气流上盘旋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's summer, and eagles effortlessly cruise the thermals,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.38,0:01:59.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,搜寻地上猎物的踪迹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}scanning the ground beneath for signs of prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.22,0:02:04.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在遥远的外蒙古大草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the distant reaches of outer Mongolia,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.78,0:02:08.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上规模最大的迁徙大军正浩浩荡荡地行进着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}one of the planet's great migrations is underway.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.94,0:02:20.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这一蔚为壮观的场面一年一次 但却很少有人亲眼目睹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Few people ever see this extraordinary annual event.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.42,0:02:29.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蒙古瞪羚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mongolian gazelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.54,0:02:34.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,共约两百万只瞪羚生活在此处 但具体数量仍不得知\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Two million are thought to live here, but no one really knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.94,0:02:40.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞪羚在大部分时间里 都各自流浪在这片广袤的大地上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For much of the time, they're scattered through this vast landscape,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.46,0:02:45.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而 每年总有一次 这些它们将会聚集在一起 繁衍后代\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but once a year they come together to have their young.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.22,0:02:50.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在接下来的十天之内 几乎所有的小家伙都会呱呱坠地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nearly all will give birth within the next 10 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.10,0:02:59.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在毫无遮挡的草原上若想安全地繁衍 最佳方法是集体照看\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0ut in the open, communal calving is the safest way to have young.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.82,0:03:02.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有了这么多双警惕的眼睛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With so many pairs of eyes keeping watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.70,0:03:05.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞪羚们能够极其有效地防止自己遭到偷袭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it's almost impossible for predators to sneak up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.06,0:03:17.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里没有矮小的灌木 也没高大的乔木 只有一样东西可以藏身其后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are no bushes, no trees. There's only one thing to hide behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.62,0:03:18.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.86,0:03:23.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草的掩护并不是非常有效\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And it's not very effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.70,0:03:35.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,掠食动物在这片空旷的草地上繁衍后代也并不轻松\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Predators also have a hard time raising their young on open grassland.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.86,0:03:40.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有了树,鹰只能直接把巢安在地面上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Without trees, eagles have to nest directly on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.34,0:03:48.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有生活在草原上的动物 都必须面对大自然残酷的一面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All the inhabitants of the Great Plains are exposed to the elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.58,0:04:08.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冲天的火光引起了一片恐慌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Fire sparks panic in the herd.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.22,0:04:20.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞪羚是天生的跑步能手, 即使是小瞪羚 奔跑速度也快过火势蔓延的速度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Gazelles are born to run and even young calves easily outpace the flames,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.54,0:04:22.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,前提条件是它们没有被困住\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}if they can avoid being trampled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.58,0:05:02.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一路无阻的大火 无情地吞噬了一切无力逃跑的生灵\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With nothing to stand in its way, the blaze consumes anything that can't flee.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.34,0:05:08.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大量的青草 宝贵的食物,片刻之间便化为乌有\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Huge quantities of grass, valuable food, have been lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.46,0:05:15.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,难逃一劫的还有老弱动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And with it, the old and the weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.46,0:05:26.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,瞪羚们远离了这片狼籍不堪的荒芜之地 继续行进 寻找新的草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The gazelles move on to new pastures and leave the desolation behind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.66,0:05:33.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宛如从灰烬中复活的凤凰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}From the ashes rises the phoenix.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.30,0:05:36.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草又匪夷所思地复活了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grass, the incredible survivor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.66,0:05:43.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草茎的基部有很强的自我保护能力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Because it grows from a protected part at the base of its stems,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.50,0:05:46.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎可以说 草是坚不可摧的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}grass is almost indestructible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:06:04.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草能迅速地自我修复 繁殖能力极强 在所有植物中 既是覆盖地球面积最大的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Able to repair and reproduce itself rapidly, it covers more of the Earth's land than any other plant
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.62,0:06:07.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又是维系生命群落种类最多的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and feeds more wildlife than any other.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.74,0:06:30.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红嘴奎利亚雀\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Red-billed quelea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.06,0:06:34.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以15亿的数量聚集在非洲的稀树大草原上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0ne and a half billion swarm across the savannahs of Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.22,0:06:38.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些鸟是地球上数量最多的鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are the most numerous birds on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.50,0:06:48.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些鸟数量众多 让它们从你的头顶上飞过要花5个小时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some flocks are so vast that they can take five hours to pass overhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.86,0:07:25.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有草才能满足这些鸟的胃口\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0nly grass can feed plagues of these proportions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.70,0:07:29.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,饥肠辘辘的群鸟贪婪地吞食着草的种子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The ravenous hordes devour the seeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.82,0:07:34.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而叶子和茎则被巨大的羚羊群所享受\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And the leaves and stems are cropped by great herds of antelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.42,0:07:50.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仅生活在东非稀树大草原的角马 就接近两百万（注：角马属羚羊的一种）\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The East African savannahs alone sustain nearly two million wildebeest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.38,0:08:05.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些角马拼命地吃草 把草根上面的草茎部分全部吃掉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They trim the grass down to its roots, leaving little in their wake,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.78,0:08:10.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而被吃掉的那部分仅在数天之内就能恢复生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but within days the plant will recover
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.74,0:08:14.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草便又继续维系着地球上 最大的动物群落的食物需要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and continue to sustain the biggest herds on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.78,0:08:29.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草不仅生长在热带地区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grass is not confined to the tropics.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.58,0:08:38.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使在北极这样恶劣的环境下草也有办法生存下来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It manages to grow even in the bitter conditions of the Arctic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.98,0:08:51.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在最后一批树木以外的地方, 处处是冰天雪地 一片荒芜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Beyond the limits of the last tree, the planet is barren and ice-locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.10,0:08:55.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是地球边缘 天寒地冻 人迹罕至\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A frozen no-man's land at the end of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.42,0:09:03.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每年却总有短短的一阵日子 漫长阴暗的冬天也会放松它的钳制\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But for a short time each year, the long, dark winter releases its grip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.14,0:09:19.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温度回升 整个寒冬都在冬眠的草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Temperatures rise
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.90,0:09:21.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又开始发芽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and grass that has lain dormant and frozen throughout the winter sprouts once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.54,0:09:29.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北极又披上了绿色的外衣\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Green returns to the Arctic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.74,0:09:36.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,眼前是一片无边无际的平原 面积相当于一个澳大利亚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The receding ice reveals an immense flat plain the size of Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.30,0:09:39.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这便是北极的苔原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the Arctic tundra.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.70,0:09:48.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然此时是万籁俱寂,一片荒凉的景象\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a desolate, silent wilderness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.98,0:09:51.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这一切即将发生变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it's about to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.74,0:10:09.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪雁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Snow geese.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.50,0:10:20.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们在墨西哥湾越冬 等到春天便一路飞过北美洲 来到这里的北极苔原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They winter along the Gulf of Mexico, and in spring they fly the entire length of North America to reach the Arctic tundra.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.74,0:10:25.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每年有五百万只雪雁都是这样迁徙\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Five million birds make this journey every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.94,0:10:46.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这场马拉松式的迁徙长达三千英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their marathon migration is almost 3,000 miles long
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.42,0:10:48.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,耗时多达三个多月\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and has taken them three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.22,0:11:00.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然早己精疲力竭 饥肠辘辘 但它们终于返回了北极圈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Exhausted and starving, they touch down inside the Arctic Circle,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.54,0:11:04.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,返回了它们阔别已久的繁殖地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}back at their traditional breeding grounds at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.02,0:11:08.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪雁一生只忠于一个配偶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Snow geese pair for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.18,0:11:13.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一对雪雁来了之后就必须取得自己的筑巢地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As soon as couples arrive, they must stake a claim to a nesting patch.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.34,0:11:22.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,理想的地方寥寥无几,邻里纠纷时常发生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Ideal sites are in short supply and quarrelsome neighbours are all around.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.22,0:11:28.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时闹得杀气腾腾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Disputes can be vicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.86,0:12:03.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,方才罢休\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Point taken!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.58,0:12:12.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北极的苔原虽然路途遥远, 但仍有短短的一段时间是食草动物的天堂\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a long way to travel, but for a short period, the tundra is the ideal place for a grazer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.26,0:12:15.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这短暂夏日 草儿茁壮生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The grass grows vigorously during the short, intense summer
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.86,0:12:18.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且这里的掠食动物比南方少多了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and there are fewer predators than further south.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.30,0:12:27.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里 雪雁可以比较放心地把巢筑在地上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here, geese can nest on the ground in relative safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.18,0:12:31.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而 雌雪雁必须花三周的时间孵蛋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nonetheless, this female must incubate her eggs for three weeks
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.22,0:12:34.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而在这三周里 它将变得易受攻击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and throughout this time she will be very vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.90,0:12:52.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一头北极狐在雪雁的领地附近逡巡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An Arctic fox surveys the colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.02,0:12:54.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它已经等了整整一个冬天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She's been waiting for the geese all winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.18,0:13:02.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,出其不意的偷袭很难奏效\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sneaking up unnoticed is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.90,0:13:15.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许命运之神会眷顾勇敢的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Perhaps fortune will favour the bold.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.46,0:13:34.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪雁的领地防御完善,很难让狐狸轻松下手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The colony is well-defended. There are no easy pickings here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.02,0:13:48.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只狐狸四处碰壁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She's driven away from every nest, but hunger compels her to continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.54,0:13:51.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但在饥饿的驱使下始终不肯放弃努力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are more eggs here than she can possibly eat now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.78,0:14:22.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的蛋多得它根本吃不了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the nesting season is short.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.78,0:14:25.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是雪雁的繁殖季很短\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So she stashes much of her plunder for later in the year
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.06,0:14:30.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以狐狸会把蛋藏起来 以作雪雁迁徙之后的食物之用\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}when all the geese have gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.26,0:14:46.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在北极苔原更远的南边有更大的掠食动物出没\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Further south, other bigger predators prowl the tundra.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.38,0:14:50.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Wolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.50,0:14:54.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于狼来说 在茫茫大草原上寻食甚至更为艰辛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For them, finding food on the plains is an even greater challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.02,0:14:58.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不仅它们的猎物是季节性的,而且很难找到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Not only is their prey seasonal, it's also hard to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.74,0:15:02.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些狼虽觅食多日 但一无所获\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They've been searching for days without a sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.06,0:15:13.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这无边无际的大地上的某处 有它们所需要的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Somewhere in this immense landscape there is food for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.66,0:15:22.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.06,0:15:23.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北美驯鹿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Caribou.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.38,0:15:27.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,驯鹿日行30英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Travelling 30 miles a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.46,0:15:32.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,差不多整个夏季能够行进2000英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they can cover nearly 2,000 miles during the summer months.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.58,0:15:43.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狼若找不到驯鹿 就会饿死\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The wolves will starve if they don't find the caribou.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.30,0:15:48.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但若想找到这些 脚步永不停止的猎物又谈何容易？\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it's no easy task to locate prey that never stops travelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.18,0:16:14.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会叮咬它们的苍蝇以及为了寻找新草场, 驱使它们不停的向前迁徙\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Biting flies and the quest for new pasture drives the migration ever onwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.78,0:16:52.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一头狼终于找到了猎物的痕迹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A wolf has finally picked up the trail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.46,0:16:56.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,驯鹿近在眼前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The caribou are close.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.14,0:17:03.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,机会终于来了！\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At last, a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.46,0:17:08.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,猎捕开始了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The hunt is on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.22,0:17:23.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狼从受到惊吓的鹿群中寻找老弱孤残\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The wolf panics the herd, and the weak and young are singled out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.26,0:17:35.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一头小鹿和母亲失散了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A calf is separated from its mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.50,0:18:16.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在雪雁的领地,此时正值盛夏 小鸟正在孵化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the goose colony, it's high summer and eggs are hatching.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.70,0:18:23.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让人惊讶的是所有的小雪雁 差不多都在一两天内出生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The young all emerge within a day or two, a marvel of timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.38,0:18:26.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 这片领地上一下子多出了上百万只小雪雁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The colony is now home to a million goslings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.94,0:18:46.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只狐狸还在拼命地收集食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The fox is still gathering all she can get.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.10,0:18:54.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时候 一张嘴根本就不够\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sometimes one mouth simply isn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.02,0:19:31.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,总有一只难逃噩运\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0ne will have to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.10,0:19:39.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是所有的食物都要储藏起来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Not all food is stored.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.14,0:19:41.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些马上就要吃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some is needed right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.38,0:19:46.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只母狐狸有七只饥饿的小狐狸要喂养\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She has seven hungry cubs to feed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.70,0:19:54.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着小狐狸胃口不断增加\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As their appetites grow,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.30,0:19:57.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母狐狸必须拼命觅食才能养活全家\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the mother must work tirelessly to raise her family.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.46,0:20:01.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时只有健康、饱满的小狐狸 才能捱过北极的寒冬\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0nly fat, healthy cubs will survive the Arctic winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.14,0:20:20.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成千上万的小雪雁还在茁壮成长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The vast majority of the goslings are still flourishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.98,0:20:26.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们强壮得可以旅行时, 父母马上就带着它们来到更为安全的水域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their parents lead them down to the safety of the water as soon as they're strong enough to make the journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.82,0:20:36.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于狐狸来说 美好时光已经接近尾声\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For the foxes, boom time has come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.62,0:20:41.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是母亲已经给了它们一个最好的开端\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the mother has given her cubs the best possible start in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.94,0:20:46.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪雁还将一直在苔原上吃草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The geese will continue grazing the tundra
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.66,0:20:50.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到夏天结束 它们才会被迫南迁过冬\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}until the summer ends and they're forced to head south for the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.86,0:21:01.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这样的高纬度 阳光的强度非常微弱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At these latitudes, the sun's rays are weak
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.90,0:21:05.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的草儿只有几个月的生长期\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and grass can only grow here for a few months a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.46,0:21:10.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是在更远的南边 夏天的时间更长,草原更加茂盛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But further south, summers are longer and the grasslands flourish.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.94,0:21:27.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北美大草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The prairies of North America.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.78,0:21:35.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的大草原肥沃甘美 曾经养育着地球上最大的动物群落\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This rich pasture once supported the greatest herds ever seen on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.42,0:21:48.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里曾有六千万只北美野牛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There were once 60 million bison,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.14,0:21:51.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而没有哪种动物能够幸免于人类的大捕杀\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but no animal is immune to intensive hunting by man
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.86,0:21:54.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,野牛的栖息地也惨遭破坏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}or the destruction of its habitat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.38,0:21:59.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一百年前 野牛的数量曾锐减至不到一千\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And a century ago, the bison were reduced to barely 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.82,0:22:04.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今 幸亏制定了严厉的保护 这一物种的数量才得以逐步恢复\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, thanks to rigorous protection, the species is recovering.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.70,0:22:11.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的草儿生长期很长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The growing season is long,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.74,0:22:15.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够全年维系所有的动物群落的食物需要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the grass here can support herds all year round.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.42,0:22:25.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,公野牛重达一吨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Male bison weigh in at one ton.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.50,0:22:43.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在盛夏 公野牛个个吃得胖乎乎的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In high summer, the bulls are fat from the rich grazing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.78,0:22:47.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,精神焕发.然而只有为数不多的公牛会和母牛交配\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and in prime condition, but only a few will mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.50,0:22:51.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到底哪些可以交配很快就要决定了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Exactly which few is about to be decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.02,0:23:28.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在世界各个温带地区的草原上 夏季都是生长繁殖期\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0n temperate plains around the world, summer is a time for growth and reproduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.54,0:23:34.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时草花争艳\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now the grass produces its flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.82,0:23:50.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,万紫千红\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}New colours also come to the plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.26,0:24:31.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,北方的开花季节跟南半球的草原互相呼应\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The northern flowering is mirrored by the grasslands of the southern hemisphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.06,0:24:36.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天下最美丽动人的草原非南非的维尔德草原莫属\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and nowhere is more impressive than on the veldt of South Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.58,0:25:29.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并非所有温带地区的草原 在夏季都是如此五彩斑斓\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Not all temperate plains are so rich and colourful in the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.14,0:25:39.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是西藏高原的仲夏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is midsummer on the Tibetan plateau,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.66,0:25:42.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,世界上海拔最高的草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the highest great plain in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.10,0:25:52.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这样的环境里 依然生长着漫山遍野的草 维系所有食草动物的生存需要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Despite the conditions, grass survives and in sufficient quantities to support the highest of all grazing herds,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.18,0:25:54.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些是野牦牛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}those of the wild yak.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.42,0:26:00.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使在夏天 日子也并不好过\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even in summer, life is hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.06,0:26:04.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温度几乎总是在零下 空气又非常地稀薄\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Temperatures rarely rise above freezing and the air is thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.22,0:26:16.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且这里又干燥异常,那是因为一个很大的原因\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's also exceptionally dry for one very big reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.74,0:26:21.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喜马拉雅\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the Himalayas.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.62,0:26:27.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄伟的山脉犹如一道高高的屏障\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The great mountain range acts as a barrier,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.30,0:26:32.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阻挡了从南飘来的浮云 只在大地上投下了巨大雨影\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}preventing clouds moving in from the south, and this casts a giant rain shadow
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.18,0:26:35.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,西藏高原由此变得异常地干燥\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that leaves Tibet high and dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.42,0:27:00.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使风把土壤中仅存的水分带走 草也能存活下来.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grass clings to life even as desiccating winds remove what little moisture remains in the soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.34,0:27:12.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只要草能够活下来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So long as grass can survive,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.86,0:27:14.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,食草动物也能活下来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so can grazers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.94,0:27:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,藏野驴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Wild ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.02,0:27:37.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄驴在争夺领地 最有实力的也最有可能得到雌驴的青睐\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The males are fighting to win territories. Those that hold the best are more likely to attract a herd of females.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.62,0:27:56.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其实是闹着玩的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a frisky business.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.14,0:28:02.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那样算是胜了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}That counts as a victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.62,0:28:05.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但却没有看到雌驴的出现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but he can't assume the females will actually turn up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.42,0:28:14.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雌野驴是一种神秘的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Female asses are mysterious creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.34,0:28:23.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随兴而来随兴而去 对于外人来说 这些雌驴的脾性好像是不可捉摸的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They come and go as they please and much of their behaviour seems unfathomable to an outsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.30,0:28:37.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是高原上的伟大游牧民族\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're the great nomads of the plateau
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.90,0:28:42.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了寻找绿洲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and will often trek vast distances across these parched plains
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.42,0:28:45.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其足迹早己遍布整个西藏高原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}in search of oases.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.82,0:28:48.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当这些野驴真地找到了新的天地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But when they do find paradise,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.10,0:28:51.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,饮水的饮水 吃草的吃草 个个毫无留恋之情\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they are liable to feed and drink for just a few hours
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.78,0:28:55.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数小时后就绝尘而去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and then head back to the dust for no apparent reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.26,0:29:05.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,野驴是高原边疆上最明显的拓荒者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Wild ass are the most conspicuous pioneers of this high frontier,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.30,0:29:09.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但数量最为可观的食草动物却深藏在地下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the most numerous grazer in Tibet lives underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.46,0:29:18.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鼠兔 兔子的亲戚,和兔子一样以草为食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Pika, a relative of the rabbit. It, too, feeds on grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.18,0:29:26.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在毫无遮挡的草原上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0n the exposed plateau,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.18,0:29:28.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鼠兔从不敢远离自己的洞穴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}pikas never stray far from their burrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.98,0:29:33.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是尽管如此 鼠兔的洞穴还是经常被其它动物霸占\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But even so, squatters will move in given half a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.58,0:29:50.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而尽管啄地鸟和雪雀鸠占雀巢的行为确实很讨厌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}While ground peckers and snow finches can be a nuisance,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.46,0:29:55.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们还是值得忍受的 它们可以在危险来临之前给鼠兔预先的警告\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they're worth tolerating because they provide a valuable early warning system.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.06,0:30:13.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长相怪异的藏狐 鼠兔的灾星\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The bizarre Tibetan fox. The pika's nemesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.90,0:30:39.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在蹑手蹑脚地潜近猎物时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}When stalking, it keeps below the skyline,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.00,0:30:43.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,藏狐能保持特别低的姿势 可能其古怪的体型起了一定的作用\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}perhaps helped by its curious body shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.98,0:30:47.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是为什么是方形的头呢？\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But why the square head?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.82,0:31:40.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在夏季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.06,0:31:42.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,西藏高原温度升高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the Tibetan plateau heats up,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.22,0:31:45.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南方的温湿空气随之而来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}drawing in warm, wet air from the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.38,0:31:48.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是雨水却从不光顾这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the water never arrives.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.18,0:31:52.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,潮湿的空气上升遇到雄伟的喜马拉雅山后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the moist air approaches, it's forced upwards by the Himalayas
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.38,0:31:55.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,便凝聚成为巨大的积雨云\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and condenses into huge rain clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.26,0:32:14.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雨全都下在喜马拉雅山南边的山峰上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These clouds drop all their water on the southern side of the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.26,0:32:21.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是这些山峰的存在使得西藏变得气候干燥 也造成了季风雨只落在更远的南方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The very peaks that keep Tibet dry are responsible for the monsoon rains falling farther south
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.74,0:32:24.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,令印度的大地显得一片绿意盎然\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the greening of India.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.02,0:32:37.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里 伴着雨水的滋润,沐浴在灿烂的阳光下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here, soaked by rain and bathed in tropical sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.90,0:32:40.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,萋萋芳草生机无限\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}grass reaches its full potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.34,0:32:46.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,象草是世界上最高的草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Elephant grass is the tallest in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.10,0:33:01.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种草长得比大象还高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grass that towers over an elephant
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.66,0:33:04.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,里面可以隐藏各种各样的秘密\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}can conceal all sorts of surprises.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.66,0:33:15.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄性孟加拉鸨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The male Lesser Florican.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.94,0:33:21.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这么高的草丛里面求偶是很难得到关注的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's hard work getting noticed when you go courting in high grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.50,0:33:36.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地处热带的印度 有着茂盛的草原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The long-grass plains of tropical India
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.98,0:33:41.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草原上生活着世界上最大的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are home to some of the largest grass-eating mammals on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.54,0:33:44.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和最小的食草类哺乳动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And some of the smallest.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.02,0:33:49.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,姬猪的大小和兔子不相上下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Pygmy hogs are no bigger than rabbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.18,0:33:52.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种猪是世界上最稀有的、体型最小的野猪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're the tiniest and rarest of all wild pigs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.78,0:34:00.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只母猪正忙着把草收集起来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The female is busy collecting grass,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.38,0:34:02.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过这不是为了填饱肚子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but not for eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.42,0:34:11.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是为了筑巢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She's building a nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.38,0:34:30.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每一只小猪都小得可以放在手掌心上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each piglet may be small enough to fit in the palm of a hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.54,0:34:32.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但母猪确生了有10只小猪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but she does have 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.46,0:34:51.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里让我们见识到了如果有足够的阳光和雨水 草能够长到什么程度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is how grass can grow, given unlimited sunshine and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.54,0:34:58.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而地球上的绝大多数热带草原 在经历雨季后总是要经历旱季的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But on most tropical plains across our planet, the wet season is followed by a dry one.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.62,0:35:10.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在非洲的稀树大草原上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0n the African savannahs,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.34,0:35:14.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,食草动物正浩浩荡荡地行进着 去寻找草和水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}grazers are marching in search of grass and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.34,0:35:39.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于缺乏雨水 这里的草原变成了黄尘地带\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Without rain, these plains can become dust bowls.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.42,0:35:42.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草现在也许会被连根拔起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grass can now lose its hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.06,0:35:57.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大象的生命变得岌岌可危 因为它们几乎每天都要喝水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Elephants are in immediate danger. They must drink almost daily.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.02,0:36:04.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在干渴的驱使下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Driven on by thirst,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.62,0:36:08.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们在干涸的平原上跋涉几百英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they march hundreds of miles across the parched plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.62,0:36:35.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,领头的老雌象 凭着记忆 带领全家大小去寻找以前救过它们的水坑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Relying on memory, the matriarchs lead their families to those special water holes that saved them in previous years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.90,0:36:44.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个还有水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This one still has water,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.50,0:36:48.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可大象必须和其它照样渴得要命的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they must share what remains
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.62,0:36:50.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,分享所剩无几的资源\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}with desperately thirsty animals of all kinds.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.98,0:37:09.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这时候正是紧张时刻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are tense times.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.86,0:37:32.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大象在这些水坑的控制权上占主导地位 但随着夜幕降临力量的对比将发生变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The elephants dominate the water hole, but as night falls the balance of power will shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.94,0:37:50.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,口干舌焦的动物趁着夜色纷至沓来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Thirsty herds continue to arrive throughout the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.14,0:37:52.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,夜间行路比较凉爽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a cooler time to travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.78,0:38:16.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在黑暗之中 局势发生了变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the darkness, the tables turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.58,0:38:23.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大象的夜视能力只比人类稍好一点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The elephant's night vision is little better than our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.70,0:38:30.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而狮子有着更加锐利的视力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But lions have much more sensitive eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.46,0:38:47.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狮子十分饥饿 大象好像也感觉到了危机\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The cats are hungry and the elephants seem to sense it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.06,0:39:30.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狮子通常不会把大象当作捕杀对象\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Lions don't usually hunt elephants,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.18,0:39:34.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但到了走投无路之时也会铤而走险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but desperate times require desperate measures.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.14,0:39:39.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这一象群里有更容易下手的幼象\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This herd contains calves, easier targets.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.70,0:39:45.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是怎样才能接近呢？\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But how to reach them?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.50,0:40:03.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成年象已经围成圈在保护小象\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The adults encircle their young.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.14,0:40:06.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这堵灰色皮墙围得非常坚固 很难突破\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's an impenetrable wall of grey.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.86,0:40:37.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有一些筋疲力竭的落伍的大象赶了过来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A few exhausted stragglers are still arriving.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.46,0:40:44.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中一头落单了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}0ne of them is alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.50,0:41:06.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是由于它的体型太大了 狮子对付不了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it's too big for the lions to tackle.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.30,0:41:14.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这头看起来小一点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This one looks a little smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.66,0:41:30.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一只单枪匹马的狮子是根本没有办法的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A solitary lion stands no chance,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.66,0:41:33.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是现在整个狮群都已倾巢出动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the whole pride is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.62,0:41:41.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们有三十只之多 如此的数量就变成了捕杀大象的专家\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are 30 of them and they are specialist elephant hunters.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.50,0:42:52.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这头大象足以供整群狮子至少吃一周\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This elephant will feed the whole pride for at least a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.94,0:43:05.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大象知道这里的水坑很危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Elephants know these drinking holes are dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.70,0:43:07.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但没有办法\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.46,0:43:17.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,刚刚播放的残酷的画面提醒着我们 水对于草原上的生命是何等重要啊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The dramas that play out here are a savage reminder of how important water is for all life on these plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.70,0:43:28.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旱季接近尾声\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the dry season finally draws to a close,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.66,0:43:33.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经受了太阳烘烤的非洲稀树大草原 发生了天翻地覆的变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Africa's baked savannahs undergo a radical change.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.82,0:43:42.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大雨横扫整个非洲大地 于是生命力极其顽强的草 又复活了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Rain sweeps across the continent and grass, the great survivor, rises again.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.10,0:43:44.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,动物又成群结队而来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And the herds return.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.94,0:43:54.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些动物曾接连数月 守着零落四方的小水坑 过着艰难的生活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For months they've been scattered over huge areas, clinging to existence around tiny water holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.22,0:43:58.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在好时光又来了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, the good times are back.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.10,0:44:07.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一些地方非常特别\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A few African savannahs are very special.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.78,0:44:13.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这些平坦的草原上 四面八方的雨水汇聚在一起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here, rainwater from far and wide flows across the flat plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.06,0:44:18.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草被淹在水里 却依然生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grass is submerged, but still it grows.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.22,0:44:42.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,洪水淹不死 大火烧不死 烈日晒不死 冰雪冻不死\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Flooded, burnt, baked and frozen,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.10,0:44:44.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草能承受一切的苦难\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}grass can withstand it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.70,0:44:55.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,六个月的旱季过后 如茵的绿草再一次覆盖了尘嚣大地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After six months of drought, grass replaces dust over great areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.18,0:45:10.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小草发芽了 动物们全都闻风而来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Fresh new shoots draw animals from great distances.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.26,0:45:26.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很多动物都不远万里前来 美好的时光谁也不愿错过\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Many undertake epic migrations to catch the boom time.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.66,0:45:39.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有一些有本领的动物一年到头就生活在这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some resourceful animals live here all the year round.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.58,0:45:49.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狒狒就是长年居住在这里的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Baboons are permanent residents,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.34,0:45:55.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但若想在这块刚被洪水淹没的草原上觅食 狒狒也得改变自己的习性\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they have to change their behaviour if they are to gather what they need on the newly flooded plains.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.30,0:46:05.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里到处都有吃的 但要到手还真有点棘手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's plenty to eat, but getting to it can be a little uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.66,0:46:58.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然水给小家伙们带来了新的麻烦\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}New water poses problems for the youngsters,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.38,0:47:01.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是它们知道要怎么才能找个干燥的位子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they know where to find a dry seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.10,0:47:16.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了鲜美多汁的蜗牛把爪子弄湿也值得\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Ajuicy snail is ample recompense for sodden paws.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.14,0:47:33.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经历了干旱贫脊之后 动物们现在可以享受成果了.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Having survived the dry, barren times, animals can now reap the rewards.
